Differential diagnosis. This species is similar to P. c e c h i
Boczek & Michalska, 1989
, but can be differentiated by the dorsal and ventral annuli with tapered microtubercles (dorsal annuli smooth, ventral annuli with elliptical microtubercles in
P. cechi
); coxal plates with short lines and granules (coxal plate I with indistinct curved lines, coxal plate II smooth in
P. cechi
); prosternal apodeme present (hind coxae separated not forming sternum in
P. cechi
).
